author: ERIC STEPHENS
title: Predators push Ducks back to square one with easy 5-1 win
text: Predators push Ducks back to square one with easy 5-1 win Oct. 22, 2015 Updated 7:38 p.m. 1 of 7 Predators left wing Eric Nystrom (24) scores against Ducks goalie Anton Khudobin in the second period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Predators forward Mike Fisher falls over Ducks right wing Corey Perry in the first period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Ducks left wing Patrick Maroon (19) and Nashville Predators defenseman Mattias Ekholm (14) battle for the puck in the first period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Predators center Mike Ribeiro (63) celebrates with Roman Josi (59), of Switzerland, and Colin Wilson (33) after Ribeiro scored against the Ducks in the second period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Ducks center Ryan Getzlaf (15) and Predators defenseman Roman Josi (59) chase the puck in the first period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Predators defenseman Ryan Ellis, second from right, is congratulated by teammates Craig Smith (15) and Seth Jones (3) after scoring against the Ducks in the second period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS 1 of 7 Predators left wing Eric Nystrom (24) celebrates with teammates Austin Watson (51) and Paul Gaustad, center, after scoring against the Ducks in the second period. MARK HUMPHREY, THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
